values: moar funny pictures The picture is a picture of my cat, Pre by the way.

I have to say that so far, today has actually been a good day. Went down to my local jobcentre this morning after preparing an argument as to say why I do not want to go on New Deal (its because of the course provider, A4E. They are useless, evil arseholes who have nothing better to do than waste your time and insult you to no end. Plus, your stuck in with a pile of drug addicts, alcoholics and much more) when the woman sorting it all out actually referred me to the course which I wanted to attempt, was offered to me and I got through the referral. I now have an interview and a test to go through next week but I should already be on this scheme as soon as I pick out the job I want to go into. Then I will get paid £5.80 per hour, twenty five hours per week for twenty six weeks. And obviously I still have SWIM sessions and signing to attend until I'm fully on the scheme. Can't wait.
And no, I'm not some jobless scum. I have been applying and attending interviews. Last one was for Greggs which I didn't get. I did everything right though which happened to annoy me. Anyway, not much else has been going on besides that. Going out on Thursday with my friend, Skye where I will hopefully buy a pair of fishnet tights, an Alice in Wonderland T-shirt and a new pair of jeans since I'm running out. Also going to likely go out to dinner as well.
I guess thats it for now. Stay tuned. :P

Sat down now at this minute on the sofa on my laptop and watching Smallville Series 3 Episode 1 on ITV2. It's boring. I hate being ill. Went to the Doctors Surgery today as well and found that through the NHS I am allowed to have part of the nail removed on both toes. Kept saying "Toe" instead of "Toenail" earlier so I think I confused a few people as often it would come out as "I am having my toe removed..." followed by the usual curse word at my own mistake lol. Have to wait for several months before I get the letter which will probably refer me to the Royal Gwent or to Panteg Hospital. I won't be able to walk well for a week or so. I just hope that it won't get in the way of college and exams or even the holiday to Turkey...Otherwise I'm going to be limping and everyone else is going to be in front of me...
Currently have a headache and a bad stomach so can't really stay on here long. Rang up the college today to say I am absent for the whole day...going into college tomorrow...

Really annoying as have now missed the start of college due to appointments with the doctor, yet one was concerning my blood pressure and the other is going to be concerning a rather icky in-grown toenail which hurts like hell and now bleeds. I've been cutting it as well but I've had it since I was ten or eleven and it hasn't even tried to correct itself at all. Still hurting now and was kept up for most of the night due to the evil thing bleeding so I am going to see if I can get it cut in a bit. There's a high risk of infection from that so if that is the case, I get to have it done in what I would assume would be Panteg Hospital and I am sorry to my friends if I have to spend more time off college. I really don't want to now at all. 
There's that and also the fact that perhaps I am beating myself up a little here for what happened to my mother's friend. I saw her in hospital yesterday. She did look better but I tend to now think that I should have checked up on her myself as unlike my mother who fell back asleep, I couldn't sleep for ages on that night (a little like last night...fell asleep at four o'clock in the morning :( ), made sure that she was at least really okay and then phoned the ambulance myself. The amount of blood was really bad and we found out yesterday that four veins had burst inside her which was why she was vomiting blood. And also her liver is really damaged but luckily enough it hadn't affected her kidney's that much. Today apparently she is having a scan on the liver to see how bad it really is and whether it will be able to repair itself. My father also asked me last night if I was happy that I got to see her in hospital and I told him "No. I would only be happy when she comes out of hospital." 

That's all for now I think...

Got woken up this morning by the ambulance and my mother shouting in my ear telling me that her friend (who is an alcoholic) had gone to hospital because she kept vomiting up serious loads of blood which isn't good. I think I know what she's done to the liver as well which makes it worse because the disease is dangerous. Now just feel sick because I had to clean up the bathroom which stank of blood and it was everywhere as well. Just ended up writing out chapters three and four for my new story, "Ange de Sang - Blood Angel" for Fictionpress, Deviantart and my friend's site Aesthesia. Intend to finish this one and I know I have said that a lot before but I do have a rather solid idea in my head for this one, using one of my old characters that I decided to sort of revamp and pretty much use that story and some of the old parts to turn him into that character. It's quite hard to develop a character like that but as I said...I have the whole thing planned for a change which is good. 
Ugh, mother just asked me to go into my brother's room and the blood was all over his bed and all. Worse, had to pick up the sheets...the smell made me feel ill again. What's not good about that is that I hardly eat anything at the moment because of my stupid diet. I have breakfast, dinner and tea though so don't worry...I hate diets!

I haven't been here in a while so sorry about that really. I guess I haven't really been doing much since the last post last year. Still no job as my father won't let me get one until I come back from Turkey just in case they won't give me the time off. I didn't even want to go to Turkey and my parents bought me a place on the holiday without even asking me about it in the first place. That really did piss me off to be perfectly honest, now I am going on a holiday that I probably won't enjoy as much due to the fact that my father is definitely going. Reason for that is because he still treats me like a child but I am 19 years old now, able to look out for myself. Gareth maybe a lot older than me but they don't force a holiday that he doesn't want or anything else like that on him, neither do they do the same to Damian. No, they just pick on me because I am the youngest which is most definitely unfair! People would say that's life and I know that but there should be at least a choice that should be made in these types of situations. Also they booked a one bedroom apartment! If they have a sofa, I'm taking it and I don't care about discomfort, I am not sleeping in a room with my parents. Privacy should be respected. If that is definitely the situation then I am changing in the bathroom, no matter how small or slippery it is and if someone calls me a "weirdo", oh well, like I give a damn anyway! 
I guess I am very angry with them for doing this and I don't have much money at all so I don't know how I will survive without having a job now. They want me to move out as well and I definitely want to go from here. I hate it here, hate being treated like shit because I am different to others. People should be individual, not clones and there is far too many people who think being a clone is the best damn thing on this earth! It isn't for christs sake! Whats a good thing for this planet is looking after it, not making it become worse, which we, as a human race, have very well done! I've just switched my bank statements to on-line only which is going to be my part along with recycling to look after this planet. I already have a phobia with the dark which my parents did not help me get over at all when I was growing up. Now I can't sleep in the dark at all! I suppose I could try sitting in a room in the dark for a good duration of the time and see how I go? I just don't know anymore.

Going to see War of the Worlds live on stage in the CIA in Cardiff on that date. I admit to actually feeling excited about going as I am the crazy person who wants to get zapped by that Tripod they put on stage. 
Okay in other news mother had a go at me on Tuesday because I'm apparently lazy and stupid and I should get a job. Sorry for being alive. Sorry but you're not HELPING me. Thats what I wanted to say to her but my mother has an attrocious temper (I think thats how its spelled...) Anyway, was forced to do loads of laundry and clean out my room yesterday and now today I am tired. 

Got to go put the hoover around now. Stupid really as I am eighteen and I should be entitled to make my own decisions, not have my parents butt into my life continuously!  

P.S. I'm really getting into this band called 30 Seconds to Mars...if you haven't heard anything by them, I seriously suggest you check them out.

Yeah my friend, Jade gave me A for this Meme-gen thing!

Leave a comment and I'll give you a letter; then you have to list 10 things you like starting with that letter. Post them in your journal and give out new letters to your commenters in turn. NO TAGBACKS ALLOWED, unless a commenter specifically requests to be given a letter!

1) Aerosmith! (awesome band!)
2) Audioslave...
3) Audio in general...I mean you need it for sound basically!
4) Anne Rice (she has wrote some cool books.)
5) An American Werewolf In London
6) All The Right Reasons (album by Nickelback)
7) Axel from Kingdom Hearts, he rocks my socks off!
8) Arkham
9) Ariel (from the little mermaid...my favourite disney movie)
10) Aladdin!

So gimme some comments and I will give you a letter...

Was supposed to go looking for a job today but at the last minute, mum backed out, saying that we could look next week instead. There was nothing to do then so I stayed on the computer all day after writing up my Final Fantasy VII Songfic for ff.net. Have lost ten pounds in weight. Feel great for it as I might have said before. Went out to Hay-On-Wye yesterday. The town was too small and expensive for my liking. A normal jumper there cost one hundred pounds. How the hell? Thats more expensive than Cardiff and London put together and that pretty much adds up to one huge statement trust me. Went to look around Talgarth in the car then. That was a waste of time since its worse than Pontypool. Was going to go to Brecon but Malcomn kept saying that there was nothing there for us to see when it could have been a pretty big town for all we know. 
So we stopped off at this really fancy restaurant. Could tell that mum had been drinking since she was trying to get me to drink wine with my dinner. She can't seem to understand that I don't drink anymore, even if I wasn't dieting. I don't wanna go back that way at all. People say a look slimmer but I don't know now. I look the same! One day I want to go to either Hereford or Cardiff, just for a bit of peace from my parents...

Anyway...sorry for writing up a huge complaint, yet I thought that I could share my views with others...so here you go really.

Yeah, took ages with the layout but I hope that eveyrthing is okay with it now. In other news, just finally managed to get two weeks off for the Easter break, something that we all deserve. Got a problem with it though. Gotta do sucky homework which has been set by each of my tutors. 
Oh and Jade, do not laugh at the layout...lol
just a test of the new image!

Been ill all week with what seems like the worst Cold in a year since I hardly ever catch them anymore thanks to those Flu jabs the evil nurses keep insisting I have every time I have an asthma review. Been off College all week. Maybe off tomorrow as well and won't be able to go Friday due to a stupid third repeat of a blood test for a problem from ages ago which I am now also having problems with because I haven't reached my "time" for this month yet and I was meant to have it last week. Apparently the second vial for my second repeat was smashed during delivery to the laboratory and they hadn't even bothered to tell me until I decided to phone them up and ask what the hell was going on!
Sorry Jade, if you are reading this, can you do me a favour please? Can you tell Jeremy I won't be in Friday because of a Blood Test and also pick up the necessary sheets needed for the work? Sorry to be a bother...feeling a lot better now but still have this annoying cough and a sore throat that makes me feel as if I have two holes in my throat. Apparently I get all these silly little virus things worse most of the time when I catch them because of my stupid Asthma.I sound like I am complaining. I'll be quiet now.

Yeah, this week has been strange. Except for today, had practically the whole week off from college because my teacher can't come in because of a teachers conference in London. Nice place that, wish I could live there instead of in the city of the damned that is Pontypool. Really, really can't wait to move now. Still need a damn job though. Best exitement of this week was that I went to the "The John Capel Hanbury Pub" or "Weatherspoons" with my friend Jade. Odd thing was I didn't really know until I had ordered a Pepsi for her and a WKD for myself(only like Vodka Blue...don't like any other alcopops really since they all seem to taste the same to me) that we were gonna order breakfast. Must have looked like an alcoholic then which I am not. Went into College today. Had an asthma attack so went home as soon as Tom could pick Sarah, Dave and I up to go into town. Hate town as I said, only interesting place is the Wiccan shop "Buzz".Lots of books on meditation but wasn't exactly what I was looking for. A friend has agreed to lend me her book of spells so I know what I'm dabbling into. Not an actual witch just find it all terribly interesting and useful for my written works that possibly need desperate finishing at this moment in time. The one I am working on right now is my favourite though. Don't exactly know why but I feel like I can relate to it. guess its because I know what it is like to be different in a place that is full of a population who believe that they have to be the same thing over and over. Get frequent insults thrown at me just because I wear lots of black. Don't really care since at the end of the day its what I feel like I should dress as at the moment. Guess moving is going to be a good idea if I can get enough money rounded from all kinds of jobs...

Yeah, I'm actually back, but not so alive and kicking. i have actually come down with a virus that has brought on a chest infection which is being a bitch because it is refusing to go. My friends in college are apparently arguing over something one of them had spread about me. Well i don't care and I actually want out of the whole arguments thing so I'm not getting involved.
I am also trying to get a part-time job as a cashier in a supermarket but it is hard because way to many people like that job so I will probably end up working somewhere like Wilkinsons which is not too bad I guess. 
Plus, I seem to be writing more stories than ever and by the end of the month, will probably post some up onto here.

ya i'm back now and have finally got to final fortress with Team Sonic. Have also gotten past Mystic Mansion as Team Chaotix and is now stuck on Egg Fleet. Worst of all my GCSES have started and I fucking hate them.

I am finally on Egg Emperor as Team Dark and is very slowly beating him. Had to finish my Art exam today. It was boring but the work was bloody easy. Mrs Hyne threw Emma's Snowboard for her coursework behind the cupboard because it is crap and not finished. Bitch deserved it. Also, my supposed friend, Roxanne had a go at me today because I wasn't serving any customers for our little stall. Well you can fucking tell me off any time other than when I am in the middle of an exam and your stress levels are high because you spilled water all over the desk twice on accident.

I have an Art exam on Monday and Tuesday and Mrs Hyne is a bitch. She always expects people to get their work done in one minute lol. Anyway, my friend has been kicked out of that exam because she had to much time from school and a girl that i hate has been beaten up....finally!

I have teachers training day today although it doesn't feel like it. Mam and Dad have gone to a funeral while I'm stuck here watching Charmed which is a cool show but now I end up being stuck on the computer because there is crap all on T.V. Oh, oh, oh Smallville tonight.....YAY!!!!!!! 
Anyway, had to start revising for Biology. The subjects I am mostly focused on are English, Biology, Chemistry, Physics, Eng. Lan., Eng. Lit, Art, History and Maths but I have to revise my French Oral as well so I feel pretty fucked up. Gcses start in May but our French Oral is starting this week I think and the AArt exam is next week. Two full days, I think I am going to die. I almost did in the mocks, it was boring as hell.

I finally have it. I'm so happy lol. Changed my picture today. Cool isn't it. It's a picture of Dante from Devil May Cry 3 which is my favourite game at the moment. Today was quite boring. Fucked up my picture of Dante because I ran out of the colour I had to use on his face. 
I also heard that an arsehole that lives over the road from my house has been warned that if he doesn't pay a fine for an assault on his next door neighbour, he's going to be arrested and forced to pay it which is quite good. 
Not looking forward to school on Tuesday even if it is tuesday.
